The paper introduces a neural network architecture for end-to-end differentiable proving of queries to knowledge bases. This involves combining symbolic reasoning with learning subsymbolic vector representations. Therefore, the most likely sub-categories are cs.AI (Artificial Intelligence) and cs.LG (Machine Learning), which are both concerned with developing intelligent systems that can learn and reason. The paper also involves natural language processing (NLP) and knowledge representation, which are covered by cs.CL (Computation and Language) and cs.DB (Databases), respectively. Finally, the paper uses gradient descent to train the neural network, which falls under cs.NE (Neural and Evolutionary Computing).
